<bioghist encodinganalog="545$a">
<head>Historical Information
</head>
<p>The "First Baptist Church" of Richmond was established in 1780 comprised of both White and African American members. In 1841, the White members spit from the congregation to from a separate church at 12th &amp; Broad, and the African American congregation would come to be known as "First African Baptist Church" of Richmond.
</p>
</bioghist>
<scopecontent encodinganalog="520$a">
<head>Scope and Content
</head>
<p>Church Records,1714 - 2002, of The First Baptist Church of Richmond, Virginia.  The collection includes records from both the First Baptist Church and First African Baptist Church comprised of bulletins, correspondence, financial records, letters, newspaper clippings, and photos. The records detail the history and organization of the churches.
</p>
</scopecontent>
